Step 1 - Install terraform

Command:

--> wget -O - https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg
--> echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg] https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com $(grep -oP '(?<=UBUNTU_CODENAME=).*' /etc/os-release || lsb_release -cs) main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/hashicorp.list
--> sudo apt update && sudo apt install terraform.

STEP 2 - Now install and configure AWS and provide the Access key ID and secret access key ID which will be available in security options in AWs account.

STEP 3 - Now create shell using .tf extension

Command: 

vim main.tf

STEP 4 - Now write the script to create EC2 instances.

Script:
 
provider "aws" {
        profile = "default"
        region = "us-east-1"
}
resource "aws_instance" "organization" {
        ami = "ami-0d86c69530d0a048e"
        instance_type = "t3.micro"
}

STEP 5 - Come out of shell and initiate the terraform

Command:

terraform init

STEP 6 - Now view the version to see what version is terraform

Command:

terraform version

STEP 7 - Now view the plan

Command:

terraform plan

STEP 8 - Now apply the terraform 

Command:

terraform apply

Step 9 - Now destroy (if applicable)

terraform destroy
